FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE - BULGARIA (15): (BURGAS) NEW OUTBREAK
*************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

[1]
Date: Sat 19 Mar 2011
Source: FOCUS Information Agency [edited]
<http://www.focus-fen.net/index.php?id=n244956>


The Agriculture and Food Ministry announced that 143 cows have tested
positive for foot-and-mouth disease (FMD) in southeastern Bulgaria,
close to the border with Turkey.

The animals live on a farm outside any community, in a forest. The
infection most probably spread from wild animals. The farm is located
close to the village of Kirovo [Burgas province], southeastern
municipality of Sredets, the Bulgarian Food Safety Agency said.

The animals in the village are out of danger for now, because they
have not been in contact with any of the above-mentioned cows. No
quarantine will be imposed in the region. All 143 cows will be killed
and their owner will be paid compensations, the agency added.

--
